<Sect1 Id="SMModifyPaletteDialogDE">
<Title>Style Manager Modify Color Dialog Box</Title>
<IndexTerm><Primary>Style Manager Modify Color Dialog Box</Primary></Indexterm>
<IndexTerm><Primary>modifying palettes</Primary></Indexterm>
<IndexTerm><Primary>palettes, modifying</Primary></Indexterm>
<Para><Anchor Id="modifyPaletteDialog">
</Para>
<Graphic Entityref="ModifyDialogBox" Id="HSTYM.REF.fig.5"></Graphic>
<Para>When you change the settings in this dialog box, you change a color in
the currently selected palette. If you have a default palette (one of the
palettes provided with the desktop) selected, you may want to copy it
before you adjust the palette. (See
<XRef Linkend="CreatePaletteTA">.) This ensures that you can return to the original settings
of the default palette if necessary.
</Para>
<VariableList>
<VarListEntry>
<Term>Old</Term>
<ListItem>
<Para>Shows the current color.
</Para>
</ListItem>
</VarListEntry>
<VarListEntry>
<Term>New</Term>
<ListItem>
<Para>Shows the new color as you make changes.
</Para>
</ListItem>
</VarListEntry>
<VarListEntry>
<Term>Grab Color</Term>
<ListItem>
<Para>Displays a pointer for you to choose a color in your
workspace. When you click on a color, the dialog box controls are
set to the correct values for that color.
</Para>
</ListItem>
</VarListEntry>
<VarListEntry>
<Term>R, G, B</Term>
<ListItem>
<Para>Changes red, green, and blue values.
</Para>
</ListItem>
</VarListEntry>
<VarListEntry>
<Term>Hue</Term>
<ListItem>
<Para>Changes red, green, and blue proportions.
</Para>
</ListItem>
</VarListEntry>
<VarListEntry>
<Term>Saturation</Term>
<ListItem>
<Para>Changes the color's purity.
</Para>
</ListItem>
</VarListEntry>
<VarListEntry>
<Term>Value</Term>
<ListItem>
<Para>Changes the color's brightness.
</Para>
</ListItem>
</VarListEntry>
<VarListEntry>
<Term>OK</Term>
<ListItem>
<Para>Saves changes and closes the Modify Palette dialog box.
</Para>
</ListItem>
</VarListEntry>
<VarListEntry>
<Term>Cancel</Term>
<ListItem>
<Para>Closes the dialog box without making changes. All color
settings are returned to the values they had before the dialog
box was displayed.
</Para>
</ListItem>
</VarListEntry>
<VarListEntry>
<Term>Help</Term>
<ListItem>
<Para>Displays Help about the dialog box.
</Para>
</ListItem>
</VarListEntry>
</VariableList>
<Note>
<Para>The color of text in titles, labels, lists, and text fields is toggled
between white and black depending on the settings of the Hue, Saturation,
and Value controls.
</Para>
</Note>
<Procedure>
<Title>See Also</Title>
<Step>
<ItemizedList Mark="&bull;" Role="tight">
<ListItem Id="HSTYM.REF.item.21">
<Para><XRef Linkend="ModifyPaletteTA"></Para>
</ListItem>
</ItemizedList>
</Step>
</Procedure>
</Sect1>
